summary: Finally I got my hands or a scanner. Okay, tbh I had access to one for a few days but I was too lazy to actually scan anything...
body:
Finally I got my hands or a scanner. Okay, tbh I had access to one for a few days but I was too lazy to actually scan anything 😂

Anyway, I got an inspiration to draw some Pokemon gijinkas. (I know, very original) After some consideration I decided to start from the begging and with the help of my best friend I decided to draw them with the Pokemons.

And after all the chit chat here’s Bulbasaur gijinka~ I’ll try to actually make more than just a few of these, who knows if I’d be capable of actually finishing this project (cause it’s the “smallest” project)

Pokemon Rangers, lots of action and is open to having a more serious Plot.

a Pokemon Wildlife Documentary, ie. following an up in coming Pokemon Professor on an expedition to research Pokemon in the wild 

a basic Pokemon game, follow protagonist on their adventure to collect the badges while getting swept up in the Crime Team’s plot and saving the world before becoming Pokemon Champion.

a legit, Mystery Dungeon movie, no humans, just Pokemon, and they talk and go on adventures and missions and the plot is super dark and it makes you cry!

summary:
I finished
Pokemon Ultra Sun! Was a really good game… I liked most of the additions they
did, to the story and the gameplay....
body:
I finished Pokemon Ultra Sun! Was a really good game… I liked most of the additions they did, to the story and the gameplay. Necrozma was awesome (and one-shot me the first time I tried beating it LOL), Team Rainbow Rocket was pretty fun… there were more after-game-scenes with Guzma, which was also very nice.

I think the only “mistake” in comparison to Sun and Moon I can think of right now is that they got rid of some pretty awesome scenes with and for Lillie – the scene where Lillie yells at her mother and tells her a piece of her mind was completely erased, for example, as well as the one where Lillie and the “evolved” Nebby interact so gently with each other. She also stays in Alola, instead of going onto a grand journey to see more of the world, which was… kinda sad. (I just think they took out a lot of character development for her with those scenes, she still got plenty, but also lost quite a bit this way.)

All in all, very fun game, distinct from the “original” Sun and Moon, and I’m just nagging about some missed chances for character development because I don’t understand why those were lost in the newer game. XD
